land, Netherlands":"Naaldwijk, Zuid-Holland, Nederland","Heenvliet, South Holland, Netherlands":"Heenvliet, Zuid-Holland, Nederland","Zwartewaal, Brielle, South Holland, Netherlands":"Zwartewaal, Zuid-Holland, Nederland"},"en":{"1193–1261":"1193–1261","1195–1236":"1195–1236","1195–1215":"1195–1215","1214–1263":"1214–1263","1220–Male":"1220–Deceased","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1173–1244":"1173–1244","from 1215 to 1220":"from 1215 to 1220","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","ca 1244":"about 1244","1261":"1261","ca 1189":"about 1189","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","ca 1215":"about 1215","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1236":"1236","1244":"1244","about 1214":"about 1214","about 1220":"about 1220","Naaldwijk, South Holland, Netherlands":"Naaldwijk, South Holland, Netherlands","Heenvliet, South Holland, Netherlands":"Heenvliet, South Holland, Netherlands","Zwartewaal, Brielle, South Holland, Netherlands":"Zwartewaal, South Holland, Netherlands","nameMeanings":[{"name":"van","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Anh, Thanh, Hung, Minh, Vinh, Dung, Hue, Huong, Lan, Quang, Tan, Thuy, Hong, Chi, Hang, Ho, Pok, Sang, Bai, Chin, Ching, Chu, Chuan, Dong.","Vietnamese (<b>Vạn</b>): from the Chinese surname 萬, see   Wan   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Văn</b>): from the Chinese surnames 文 or 聞, see   Wen   2 and 3, and also 5 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Wan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Yi, Qi, Qiang, Wai, Yiu, Yuk, Chien-Min, Fang, Hin, Jichun, Li, Man, Chung, Min, Yiping, Pak, Sik, Sung Man.  Vietnamese Tin, Bang, Da, Hien, Hoi, Lan, Minh Quang, Sau, Tich, Tung, Yaping, Yuet.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 萬, which means ‘ten thousand’ literally or ‘very great number’ figuratively: (i) from the personal name of Bi Wan (畢萬), an official in the state of Jin (located in present-day Shanxi province). He was said to be a descendant of Bi Gong Gao (known as Duke of Bi), the 15th son of the virtuous King Wen of Zhou (reined 1152–1056  BC ). Bi Wan was later granted the fiefdom of Wei (魏), which in 403  BC  became the state of Wei (located in present-day Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces). Some of his descendants adopted Wei (魏) as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his personal name, as their surname. (ii) from the personal name Wan (萬), style name of Rui Bo (芮伯, the Earl of Rui), an official of the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ), who was granted the fief Rui (located in Ruicheng in Shaanxi province). Some of his descendants inherited Rui (芮), the name of the fief, as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his style name, as their surname. (iii) from the placename Wan (萬), the name of a fief (located in Juxian in Shandong province) granted during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ) to an official in the ancient state of Chu. (iv) from the first element of the name of the Wan Si (萬俟) family, who lived in the downstream areas of the Yellow River during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD ). (v) from the second element of the name of the Tu Wan (吐萬) family, who are members of the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 完, meaning ‘complete’ in Chinese: (i) said to be borne by the descendants of Huan Zhui, a grandson of the Duke Huan of Song (ruler of the state of Song, died 651  BC ). (ii) from Wan (完), the name of Qu Wan (屈完), an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn Period (770–476  BC ). (iii) shortened form of the compound surname Wan-Yan (完顔), a surname from minority ethnic groups such as Juchen ethnic group in ancient northern China."]}]},{"name":"Hugo","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of   Hugh  , used throughout the Middle Ages in official documents, and now enjoying a revival as a given name."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugo I van Naaldwijk was born in 1193, in Naaldwijk, South Holland, Netherlands, his father, Bartholomeus van Voorne van Naaldwijk, was 24 and his mother, Halewijne Van Egmond, was 20. He married Gerardsdr van Velsen about 1214. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1261, in his hometown, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1193–1261":"1193–1261","1195–1236":"1195–1236","1195–1215":"1195–1215","1214–1263":"1214–1263","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1173–1244":"1173–1244","from 1215 to 1220":"1215 kuni 1220","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","ca 1244":"umbes 1244","1261":"1261","ca 1189":"umbes 1189","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","ca 1215":"umbes 1215","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1236":"1236","1244":"1244","about 1214":"umbes 1214","about 1220":"umbes 1220","Naaldwijk, South Holland, Netherlands":"Naaldwijk, Zuid-Holland, Madalmaad","Heenvliet, South Holland, Netherlands":"Heenvliet, Zuid-Holland, Madalmaad","Zwartewaal, Brielle, South Holland, Netherlands":"Zwartewaal, Zuid-Holland, Madalmaad"},"fi":{"1193–1261":"1193–1261","1195–1236":"1195–1236","1195–1215":"1195–1215","1214–1263":"1214–1263","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1173–1244":"1173–1244","from 1215 to 1220":"vuodesta 1215 vuoteen 1220","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","ca 1244":"noin 1244","1261":"1261","ca 1189":"noin 1189","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","ca 1215":"noin 1215","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","1236":"1236","1244":"1244","about 1214":"noin 1214","about 1220":"noin 1220","Naaldwijk, South Holland, Netherlands":"Naaldwijk, Zuid-Holland, Alankomaat","Heenvliet, South Holland, Netherlands":"Heenvliet, Zuid-Holland, Alankomaat","Zwartewaal, Brielle, South Holland, Netherlands":"Zwartewaal, Zuid-Holland, Alankomaat"},"fr":{"1193–1261":"1193–1261","1195–1236":"1195–1236","1195–1215":"1195–1215","1214–1263":"1214–1263","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1